On December 27, 2021, the President signed a law known as S. 1605, the "National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2022." This law primarily authorizes appropriations for the Department of Defense programs, military construction, Department of Energy national security programs, and intelligence programs for the fiscal year 2022. It also includes provisions for a military basic pay increase and other authorities related to the U.S. Armed Forces. The President expressed gratitude to Chairman Reed, Ranking Member Inhofe, Chairman Smith, Ranking Member Rogers, and the Senate and House Armed Services Committees for their leadership in this matter.